casebody.data:
Felix GARCIA, Appellant,
v.
The STATE of Florida, Appellee. No. 3D18-1054 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. Opinion filed November 28, 2018. Felix Garcia, in proper person. Pamela Jo Bondi, Attorney General, for appellee. Before EMAS, FERNANDEZ, and LOGUE, JJ. PER CURIAM.

Affirmed. See Whren v. United States , 517 U.S. 806 , 819, 116 S.Ct. 1769 , 135 L.Ed.2d 89 (1996) ("For the run-of-the-mine case, which this surely is, we think there is no realistic alternative to the traditional common-law rule that probable cause justifies a search and seizure.").
